by%20posting%20restaurant%20reviews%20and%20travel%20vlogs.%20Today%20she%20often%20blends%20her%20peppy%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecommentary%20on%20news%20she%20thinks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fstudent-explains-news-gen-zers-improve-media-literacy-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20people%20care%20about%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20healthcare%20and%20climate%20%E2%80%94%20with%20lifestyle%20content.%20In%20a%20November%20post%2C%20for%20example%2C%20she%20began%20by%20showing%20off%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40kelscruss%2Fvideo%2F7298911740899642667%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%20ribeye%20steak%20dinner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20before%20diving%20into%20an%20Athens%20Banner-Herald%20article%20about%20criminal-justice%20reform.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20newspaper%20is%20such%20a%20slay%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20user%20commented%20on%20one%20of%20Russell's%20August%20videos%20where%20she%20talked%20about%20bombs%20in%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersuading%20young%20adults%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20news%20is%20a%20daunting%20task.%20Fourteen%20percent%20of%20US%20adults%20in%20a%20September%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F11%2F15%2Fmore-americans-are-getting-news-on-tiktok-bucking-the-trend-seen-on-most-other-social-media-sites%2F%3Futm_source%3DAdaptiveMailer%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3D23-11-15%2520Package%3A%2520Social%2520%26%2520News%2C%2520News%2520Platform%2520Fact%2520Sheets%2520GENERAL%26org%3D982%26lvl%3D100%26ite%3D12925%26lea%3D2929728%26ctr%3D0%26par%3D1%26trk%3Da0DQm000000a5CTMAY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20from%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20they%20regularly%20get%20news%20from%20TikTok%2C%20up%20from%203%25%20in%202020.%20Among%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%2C%20that%20number%20jumped%20from%209%25%20to%2032%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNews%26quot%3B%20on%20TikTok%2C%20however%2C%20rarely%20comes%20from%20mainstream%20outlets%20like%20The%20Washington%20Post%20or%20NBC%20News%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20trying%20to%20build%20audiences%20there.%20The%20app's%20recommendation%20algorithm%20rarely%20pushes%20users%20toward%20these%20accounts%2C%20an%20August%20study%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F14614448231192964%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20at%20Northwestern%3C%2Fa%3E%20determined.%20%26quot%3BWe%20find%20almost%20no%20evidence%20of%20proactive%20news%20exposure%20on%20TikTok's%20behalf%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20young%20people%20on%20TikTok%20learn%20about%20what's%20happening%20from%20a%20hodgepodge%20of%20alternative%20sources%2C%20from%20commentary%20accounts%20like%20Russell's%2C%20to%20non-news%20influencers%20who%20occasionally%20dabble%20in%20current%20events%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpop-culture%2Fpop-culture-news%2Fjohnny-depp-amber-heard-social-media-defamation-tiktok-case-rcna25430%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhen%20they%20enter%20the%20mainstream%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20posts%20from%20people%20purporting%20to%20offer%20on-the-ground%20videos%20from%20breaking%20news%20events%20like%20a%20war%20or%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20TikTok's%20recommendation%20feed%2C%20there%20is%20little%20distinction%20between%20a%20report%20from%20ABC%20News%20and%20a%20rant%20about%20that%20report%20from%20a%20lifestyle%20influencer.%20That%20chaotic%20democratization%20is%20by%20design.%20A%20TikTok%20representative%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20treats%20all%20accounts%20the%20same%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20policing%20misinformation%20and%20promoting%20content.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20happens%20when%20a%20generation%20of%20Americans%20gets%20its%20news%20from%20an%20infinitely%20scrolling%20video%20app%3F%20What%20happens%20when%20the%2024-hour%20news%20cycle%20collapses%20to%20a%2024-second%20news%20cycle%3F%20In%20conversations%20with%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20TikTok%20users%2C%20creators%2C%20researchers%2C%20and%20other%20media%20stakeholders%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20Kelsey%20Russell%20filming%20herself%20flipping%20through%20the%20paper%20at%20her%20kitchen%20table%20is%20part%20of%20a%20paradigm%20shift.%20There%20are%20the%20high-stakes%20financial%20repercussions%3A%20TikTok's%20growing%20news%20influence%20could%20further%20batter%20an%20already%20severely%20wounded%20media%20industry.%20Then%20there's%20the%20potential%20dramatic%20effect%20on%20an%20informed%20republic.%20The%20app's%20ability%20to%20provide%20accurate%20information%20on%20current%20events%20is%20being%20tested%20in%20real%20time%2C%20with%20conflicts%20like%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20stretching%20TikTok's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.tiktok.com%2Fen-us%2Four-continued-actions-to-protect-the-tiktok-community-during-the-israelhamas-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtent-moderation%20bandwidth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlatforms%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20that%20interested%20in%20making%20a%20space%20for%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nick%20Hagar%2C%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20Northwestern%20report%20who%20now%20works%20as%20a%20data%20scientist%20at%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%20This%20%26quot%3Bnew%20dynamic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20impact%20what%20people%20see%20and%20what%20people%20think%20of%20as%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInfluencers%20read%20the%20news%20so%20their%20followers%20don't%20have%20to%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20core%20pillars%20of%20TikTok's%20news%20ecosystem%20is%20what%20you%20might%20call%20the%20%26quot%3Bnews%20influencer%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20creators%20like%20Russell%20who%20distill%20and%20interpret%20the%20news%20for%20their%20followers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20they're%20usually%20not%20affiliated%20with%20the%20outlets%20they%20talk%20about%2C%20these%20people%20may%20actually%20serve%20as%20better%20spokespeople%20for%20the%20industry%20than%20journalists%20at%20traditional%20publications.%20Some%20users%20told%20BI%20they%20found%20TikTokers%20more%20authentic%20and%20relatable%20than%20journalists%2C%20whom%20they%20believed%20had%20built-in%20biases%20tied%20to%20politics%20or%20corporate%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%20liked%20this%20idea%20of%20somebody%20who's%20a%20generalist%20giving%20me%20my%20news%20rather%20than%20somebody%20who's%20always%20a%20specialist%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tejas%20Sekhar%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20medical%20student%20in%20Chicago.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20sometimes%20that%20hits%20closer%20to%20home%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20I%20can%20glean%20from%20it%20that's%20relevant%20to%20my%20personal%20or%20daily%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I'm%20providing%20people%20is%20a%20near-peer%20model%20of%20education%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Russell%2C%20who%20wants%20to%20parlay%20her%20master's%20in%20sociology%20and%20education%20policy%20into%20a%20job%20that%20mixes%20entertainment%20with%20media%20literacy%20(much%20like%20what%20she%20does%20on%20TikTok%20today).%20%26quot%3BSomebody%20that%20looks%20like%20you%2C%20that%20talks%20like%20you%2C%20that%20acts%20like%20you%2C%20that%20is%20around%20your%20age%2C%20is%20able%20to%20explain%20a%20topic%20that%20you%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20understand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20US%20adults%20under%2030%20in%20Pew%20surveys%20who%20said%20they%20trusted%20information%20from%20national%20news%20outlets%20fell%20to%2056%25%20in%202022%20from%2062%25%20in%202016%2C%20with%20trust%20in%20local%20news%20outlets%20falling%20to%2062%25%20from%2071%25.%20By%20contrast%2C%20trust%20in%20information%20from%20social%20media%20rose%20to%2050%25%20from%2044%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20media%20brands%20that%20have%20been%20successful%20on%20TikTok%20often%20build%20their%20videos%20through%20individual%20reporter%20personalities.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fthe-washington-post-tiktok-account-has-a-surprisingly-popular-2019-6%3F_gl%3D1*b0ubkd*_ga*ODgyMDIyOTc4LjE2MzEwMjI2MTY.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwMTI2NTIxOS4xNjkyLjAuMTcwMTI2NTI2Ny4xMi4wLjA.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Dave%20Jorgensen%2C%20for%20example%2C%20did%20an%20entire%20video%20series%20around%20working%20from%20his%20apartment%20during%20a%20pandemic%2C%20while%20Jack%20Corbett%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanet-money-shares-strategy-for-podcast-radio-content-on-tiktok-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPlanet%20Money%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20also%20filmed%20TikToks%20at%20his%20home%20using%20a%20bedsheet%20as%20a%20green%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20TikTok's%20emerging%20class%20of%20news%20influencers%20who%20have%20created%20their%20own%20niche%2C%20reading%20traditional%20media%20is%20still%20very%20much%20a%20part%20of%20their%20daily%20habits%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20absent%20from%20some%20of%20their%20followers'%20media%20diets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%203%20million%20followers%2C%20Vitus%20%26quot%3BV%26quot%3B%20Spehar's%20%40underthedesknews%20account%20is%20particularly%20effective%20at%20bridging%20the%20divide%20between%20traditional%20media%20and%20TikTok%20news.%20The%2041-year-old%20describes%20their%20role%20on%20TikTok%20as%20a%20news%20communicator%20and%20civics%20explainer%20%E2%80%94%20a%20blend%20of%20Stephen%20Colbert%2C%20an%20after-school%20special%20on%20PBS%2C%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DOgVKvqTItto%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESchoolhouse%20Rock!%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpehar's%20videos%20often%20include%20screengrabs%20from%20news%20articles%20to%20help%20credit%20sources%20when%20talking%20about%20topics%20like%20Sam%20Altman's%20temporary%20ousting%20from%20OpenAI%20or%20a%20House%20ethics%20report%20on%20Rep.%20George%20Santos.%20Spehar%20says%20they%20monitor%20anywhere%20from%2012%20to%2015%20news%20sources%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20finding%20stories%20that%20haven't%20become%20oversaturated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA.B.%20Burns-Tucker%2C%20a%2034-year-old%20recent%20law-school%20grad%2C%20has%20a%20similar%20approach%20to%20her%20legal%20commentary%20account%20%40iamlegallyhype.%20She%20broke%20into%20TikTok%20news%20after%20posting%20a%20video%20in%20which%20she%20tried%20to%20explain%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40iamlegallyhype%2Fvideo%2F7062015965806234926%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20her%20followers%20as%20if%20she%20were%20talking%20to%20friends.%20The%20video%20took%20off%2C%20and%20she%20now%20walks%20through%20topics%20like%20an%20Israel-Hamas%20cease-fire%20or%20Mike%20Johnson's%20election%20as%20House%20speaker%20to%20an%20audience%20of%20about%20700%2C000%20followers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20post%20is%20the%20only%20way%20I%20fully%20understand%20what's%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20user%20commented%20on%20her%20October%20video%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40iamlegallyhype%2Fvideo%2F7295425857789758763%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIsrael-Hamas%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTranslators%20like%20you%20are%20so%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20user%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurns-Tucker%2C%20like%20Spehar%20and%20Russell%2C%20leans%20on%20professional%20news%20outlets%20for%20sourcing%2C%20even%20if%20her%20videos%20make%20it%20seem%20as%20if%20she's%20speaking%20off-the-cuff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20TikToker%20who%20is%20doing%20news%20communication%20has%20to%20have%20respect%20for%20traditional%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Spehar%2C%20who%20has%20done%20freelance%20work%20on%20TikTok%20for%20outlets%20like%20The%20Washington%20Post%20and%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Times.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20like%20all%20of%20it.%20But%20you've%20got%20to%20find%20one%20piece%20that%20you%20do%20like%20and%20recognize%20that%20that%20is%20what's%20giving%20you%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20TikTok%20news%20influencers%20cite%20their%20sources%2C%20of%20course.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20has%20long%20been%20the%20case%20with%20other%20platforms%2C%20sensational%20retellings%20of%20the%20news%20that%20omit%20sourcing%20details%20are%20often%20the%20most%20popular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20ridiculous%20shit%20going%20on%20around%20the%20world%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20TikTok%20creator%20named%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40davidjustinn%2Fvideo%2F6877654368087215365%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDavid%20Justinn%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20about%209%20million%20followers%20said%20in%20a%20late-2020%20video.%20%26quot%3BA%20frozen%20dragon%20was%20just%20discovered%20in%20Canada%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20notes.%20The%20video%20garnered%20about%2031%20million%20views%20and%20about%206%20million%20%26quot%3Blikes.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20on%20hot-button%20issues%20like%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%2C%20for%20example%2C%20some%20creators%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40lostmymarblesagain%2Fvideo%2F7300429846939798826%3Fq%3Dbrittany%2520broski%26t%3D1701205210882%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efelt%20pressured%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20offer%20opinions%20on%20the%20matter%20even%20if%20they%20lack%20expertise%2C%20leading%20some%20to%20distrust%20information%20from%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Pew's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2022%2F10%2F27%2Fu-s-adults-under-30-now-trust-information-from-social-media-almost-as-much-as-from-national-news-outlets%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20US%20adults%20broadly%20distrust%20information%20found%20on%20social%20media%2C%20TikTok%20faces%20an%20uphill%20battle%20given%20its%20resonance%20with%20younger%20adults%20who%20are%20more%20inclined%20to%20trust%20social%20apps.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20enlists%20fact-checking%20partners%20globally%20to%20help%20verify%20claims%20about%20misinformation.%20But%20other%20social%20apps%20have%20had%20similar%20partners%20and%20have%20failed%2C%20sometimes%20spectacularly%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fnews%2F2018%2F11%2Fmyanmar-hria%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edangerously%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20serve%20as%20effective%20news%20conduits.%20A%202020%20Pew%20report%20found%20that%20US%20consumers%20who%20turned%20to%20social%20media%20for%20news%20tended%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewtrusts.org%2Fen%2Ftrust%2Farchive%2Ffall-2020%2Famericans-who-get-news-mainly-on-social-media-are-less-knowledgeable-and-less-engaged%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20informed%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20topics%20like%20politics%20or%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20than%20their%20counterparts%20who%20engaged%20with%20traditional%20media%20like%20radio%20or%20news%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20worried%20and%20have%20a%20fear%20that%20the%20fragmentation%20that%20we%20see%20is%20going%20to%20cause%20problems%20for%20the%20body%20politic.%20That%20maybe%20people%20will%20pay%20less%20attention%20to%20politics%20and%20to%20traditional%20news%20and%20go%20off%20into%20their%20own%20corners%20on%20their%20own%20'For%20You'%20page%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gerry%20Lanosga%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20journalism%20program%20at%20Indiana%20University%20in%20Bloomington.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20survive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20traditional%20media%20%26quot%3Bhas%20to%20be%20less%20traditional%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20needs%20to%20figure%20out%20a%20way%20to%20find%20inroads%20into%20these%20platforms%2C%20exist%20on%20them%2C%20and%20even%20thrive%20in%20them%20by%20making%20news%20products%20that%20are%20more%20obtrusive%20to%20people%20and%20interesting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20prefer%20TikTok%20news%20that%20cuts%20out%20influencers%20and%20traditional%20media%20entirely%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20users%20steer%20clear%20of%20news%20commentary%20altogether%2C%20preferring%20to%20get%20information%20from%20on-the-ground%2C%20%26quot%3Bcitizen%20journalism%26quot%3B%20footage%20of%20live%20events%20or%20firsthand%20testimonials.%20These%20videos%2C%20which%20can%20be%20difficult%20for%20a%20casual%20TikToker%20to%20authenticate%2C%20are%20nevertheless%20often%20viewed%20as%20more%20genuine%20or%20authentic%20than%20information%20delivered%20by%20a%20traditional%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20see%20into%20someone's%20day-to-day%20and%20having%20them%20tell%20a%20story%20does%20feel%20so%20much%20more%20trustworthy%20or%20real%20than%20something%20that%20feels%20so%20far%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sanya%20Chaudhry%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20TikTok%20user%20in%20Toronto.%20If%20there's%20a%20way%20traditional%20media%20could%20make%20news%20%26quot%3Bfeel%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3Blike%20it's%20real%20people%20telling%20the%20stories%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20if%20they%20can%20find%20a%20way%20to%20make%20it%20more%20personable%2C%20maybe%20that's%20a%20way%20that%20more%20people%20can%20get%20engaged%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20challenging%20as%20these%20videos%20are%20to%20verify%2C%20some%20TikTok%20users%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20believed%20the%20app%20had%20built-in%20tools%20to%20keep%20bad%20actors%20in%20check.%20The%20app's%20community%20of%20users%20can%20turn%20to%20features%20like%20the%20comments%20section%20of%20videos%2C%20video%20stitching%2C%20and%20dueting%20to%20call%20out%20videos%20that%20contain%20misinformation%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20kind%20of%20peer%20policing%20community%20that%20exists%20within%20TikTok%2C%20especially%20for%20things%20that%20are%20related%20to%20social%20and%20political%20matters%2C%26quot%3B%20Sekhar%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20creators%20will%20call%20each%20other%20out%20and%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20that's%20actually%20incorrect%2C%20because%20of%20this.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20platforms%20such%20as%20Reddit%20and%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20have%20leaned%20on%20community%20features%20to%20help%20identify%20misinformation%2C%20with%20mixed%20results.%20A%20Bloomberg%20review%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fgraphics%2F2023-israel-hamas-war-misinformation-twitter-community-notes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX's%20%26quot%3BCommunity%20Notes%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%20found%20that%20the%20feature%20struggled%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20a%20relentless%20volume%20of%20misinformation%20about%20Israel%20and%20Gaza%2C%20with%20moderators%20taking%20more%20than%20seven%20hours%20on%20average%20to%20append%20corrective%20notes%20to%20false%20posts.%20In%20social-media%20time%2C%20that%20may%20as%20well%20be%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAll%20the%20news%20that's%20fit%20to%20rizz%3A%20How%20the%20media%20industry%20can%20use%20TikTok%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20form%20of%20traditional%20news%20media%20that%20TikTok%20is%20proving%20useful%20for%2C%20and%20it%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20type%20of%20journalism%20most%20crushed%20by%20the%20news%20industry's%20shift%20to%20digital%3A%20local%20journalism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTikTok%20is%20a%20better%20place%20for%20local%20stories%20than%20national%20because%20people%20log%20into%20social%20media%20to%20look%20at%20content%20specifically%20tailored%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matt%20Shearer%2C%20a%20Boston-area%20reporter%20who%20helped%20launch%20WBZ%20NewsRadio's%20TikTok%20account.%20The%20company%20won%20a%20regional%20Edward%20R.%20Murrow%20Award%20for%20innovation%20based%20on%20its%20work%20on%20the%20app%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BAny%20time%20I%20post%20a%20video%20about%20a%20small%20town%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20everybody%20in%20that%20small%20town%20and%20the%20surrounding%20towns%20shares%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Shearer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20way%20that%20radio%20is%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20flourish%20is%20if%20you%20have%20programmers%20and%20news%20directors%20who%20are%20brave%20enough%20to%20innovate%2C%20and%20try%20something%20a%20little%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20Shearer%20said.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20should%20be%20formulaic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-radio-djs-use-tiktok-find-new-listeners-2022-11%3Fr%3Dtiktok-music-lp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eradio%20hosts%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20iHeart's%20Jeffrey%20Ramsey%20in%20Denver%20or%20Shannon%20Burns%20in%20Canada%20told%20BI%20in%20November%20of%20last%20year%20that%20they%20had%20successfully%20used%20the%20app%20to%20draw%20in%20a%20broader%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20so%20far%2C%20these%20local%20journalists%20and%20a%20handful%20of%20savvy%20creators%20at%20national%20brands%20have%20been%20exceptions%20to%20the%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20vibrant%20as%20TikTok's%20news%20ecosystem%20is%2C%20the%20app%20hasn't%20done%20much%20to%20help%20the%20news%20industry%20make%20money.%20Publishers%20aren't%20holding%20their%20breath%20that%20it%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENews%20has%20long%20been%20a%20major%20headache%20for%20platforms%20like%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20uniquely%20controversial%20topic%20for%20TikTok%2C%20which%20has%20a%20China-based%20owner%20and%20is%20under%20immense%20scrutiny%20over%20the%20way%20it%20handles%20the%20flow%20of%20news%20and%20other%20information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%2C%20which%20operates%20more%20like%20an%20entertainment%20platform%20akin%20to%20YouTube%20or%20Netflix%20than%20a%20social%20network%20like%20Facebook%2C%20can%20try%20to%20avoid%20some%20of%20the%20mistakes%20in%20news%20delivery%20that%20its%20predecessors%20flubbed.%20Ultimately%2C%20it%20may%20end%20up%20re-creating%20the%20same%20information%20bubbles%20that%20plagued%20social-media%20apps%20throughout%20the%202010s%2C%20but%20this%20time%20for%20Gen%20Z.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20news%20publishers%2C%20betting%20on%20the%20app%20as%20a%20source%20to%20make%20money%20would%20be%20a%20mistake%2C%20even%20as%20TikTok%20gobbles%20up%20more%20and%20more%20user%20attention%20time%2C%20said%20Brian%20Morrissey%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20media%20newsletter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.therebooting.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Rebooting%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20was%20previously%20the%20president%20and%20editor%20in%20chief%20at%20Digiday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Google%20or%20Facebook%2C%20where%20links%20to%20news%20sites%20can%20fuel%20publishers'%20ad%20revenue%2C%20linking%20is%20almost%20nonexistent%20on%20TikTok.%20It's%20a%20closed%20ecosystem%20with%20limited%20monetization%20options%2C%20and%20TikTok%20hasn't%20expressed%20any%20interest%20in%20prioritizing%20professional%20publishers.%20The%20company%20also%20usually%20doesn't%20pay%20publishers%20for%20their%20content%2C%20though%20it%20is%20testing%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.tiktok.com%2Fen-us%2Fpulse-premiere%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ead-revenue%20share%20program%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20depending%20on%20platforms%20for%20ad%20revenues%20is%20a%20nonstarter%2C%26quot%3B%20Morrissey%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20that%20these%20tech%20platforms%20will%20help%20news%20publishers%20in%20any%20way%2C%20shape%2C%20or%20form%20to%20me%20would%20be%20a%20ridiculous%20bet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20persuading%20US%20teens%20who%20by%20one%20estimate%20spend%20an%20average%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F512576%2Fteens-spend-average-hours-social-media-per-day.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4.8%20hours%20a%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20social%20media%20to%20log%20off%20of%20TikTok%20and%20go%20directly%20to%20a%20news%20website%20they%20increasingly%20distrust%20is%20also%20a%20long-shot%20bet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERussell's%20advice%20to%20the%20industry%20is%20to%20imitate%20what%20she%20and%20her%20TikTok%20peers%20have%20done%20intuitively%3A%20Make%20the%20news%20relatable.%20Like%20any%20TikToker's%2C%20her%20videos%20are%20drawing%20eyeballs%20away%20from%20the%20very%20news%20organizations%20she%20hopes%20to%20promote.%20But%20her%20approach%20could%20also%20offer%20a%20model%20for%20how%20those%20news%20organizations%20can%20win%20over%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20time%20that%20you%20can%20bring%20in%20the%20younger%20voice%2C%20you%20can%20bring%20them%20to%20the%20table%2C%20you%20can%20make%20them%20visible%2C%20that's%20what%20people%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Russell%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20meet%20the%20people%20where%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fdan-whateley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDan%20Whateley%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20media%20reporter%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20TikTok%20and%20social%20media.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-gets-news-from-tiktok-influencers-media-industry-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702551721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65773ad058e7c0c29a2ba