ign%20and%20former%20google%20recruiter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a264450edbc52a863fb37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAnadolu%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMatt%20Opramolla%20has%20been%20a%20recruiter%20for%20over%205%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20oversharing%20during%20an%20interview%20and%20accepting%20an%20offer%20immediately%20makes%20you%20look%20desperate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKeep%20your%20answers%20concise%2C%20and%20always%20negotiate%20the%20terms%20of%20your%20job%20offer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Matt%20Opramolla%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20recruiter.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20career%20in%20sales%20and%20quickly%20transitioned%20into%20working%20for%20Indeed's%20internal%20startup%20agency%20called%20%26quot%3BIndeed%20higher.%26quot%3B%20I%20did%20well%20there%20%E2%80%94%20I%20loved%20the%20work%20I%20was%20doing%20and%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20move%20into%20corporate%20recruiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20got%20a%20job%20at%20Google%20as%20a%20recruiter.%20I%20got%20to%20hire%20and%20work%20with%20some%20of%20the%20most%20amazing%20people.%20I%20also%20got%20to%20work%20on%20really%20impactful%20scalable%20hiring%20initiatives%20across%20the%20company.%20That%20was%20one%20of%20the%20best%20parts%2C%20and%20it%20was%20my%20favorite%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20desperate%20to%20find%20work%20today%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-sweeping-the-us-these-are-the-companies-making-cuts-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emany%20layoffs%20that%20have%20happened%20this%20year.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20know%20this%20first-hand%2C%20because%20when%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20I%2C%20too%2C%20was%20desperate%20to%20support%20my%20family%20any%20way%20I%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20things%20that%20candidates%20should%20be%20aware%20of%20when%20looking%20for%20work%20%E2%80%94%20things%20that%20might%20make%20you%20look%20desperate%20to%20the%20company%20you're%20interviewing%20with.%20When%20you%20look%20desperate%2C%20employers%20might%20feel%20like%20you%20only%20want%20the%20job%20just%20to%20have%20a%20job%20and%20that%20you're%20not%20excited%20about%20their%20company%20specifically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20desperate%20also%20gives%20you%20less%20negotiating%20power%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20job%20offer.%20So%20here%20are%20three%20things%20you%20should%20stop%20doing%20and%20what%20you%20should%20do%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Asking%20for%20random%20referrals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20recruiter%2C%20I%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20random%20LinkedIn%20messages%20or%20emails%20asking%20for%20referrals%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20have%20an%20established%20relationship%20or%20connection%20to%20that%20person.%20Recruiters%20usually%20aren't%20too%20keen%20on%20those%20%26quot%3Bcopy%2Fpaste%26quot%3B%20messages.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EInstead%2C%20you%20want%20to%20be%20tactful%20and%20respectful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20better%20approach%20is%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20someone%20who%20has%20the%20job%20you%20want%20(or%20works%20on%20the%20team%20you%20want%20to%20be%20on)%20and%20have%20a%20friendly%20conversation%20with%20them.%20You%20could%20ask%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20company%20or%20a%20specific%20project%20that%20you%20know%20they're%20working%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20you%20could%20write%2C%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I%20see%20you're%20working%20on%20a%20specific%20avenue%20of%20AI%20and%20that%20really%20interests%20me.%20I%20have%20some%20thoughts%20on%20the%20topic.%20Would%20you%20be%20willing%20to%20chat%20for%2015%20to%2020%20minutes%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Then%20see%20what%20they%20say.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20won't%20get%20a%20response%20from%20everyone%2C%20but%20if%20you're%20persistent%2C%20tactful%2C%20and%20respectful%2C%20it%20can%20later%20lead%20to%20a%20relationship.%20Then%2C%20if%20that%20team%20is%20hiring%2C%20they%20will%20think%20of%20you%20for%20putting%20in%20the%20extra%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Oversharing%20in%20the%20interview%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20recruiter%2C%20one%20mistake%20I%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20interviewees%20make%20is%20oversharing%20or%20being%20unnecessarily%20transparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20it's%20not%20wise%20to%20discuss%20the%20details%20of%20a%20layoff%2C%20why%20you%20quit%20a%20former%20job%2C%20personal%20issues%20involving%20your%20finances%2C%20or%20your%20family.%20These%20things%20aren't%20relevant%20to%20your%20qualifications.%20Employers%20and%20interviewers%20are%20specifically%20trained%20not%20to%20ask%20questions%20around%20candidates'%20family%20or%20financial%20situation%2C%20so%20it's%20best%20not%20to%20bring%20it%20up.%20It's%20extraneous%20information%20that%20takes%20away%20from%20the%20focus%20of%20what%20the%20meeting%20should%20be%20about%3A%20your%20qualifications%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20think%20of%20a%20time%20where%20an%20interviewee%20said%2C%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20pay%20my%20rent%20in%20two%20months%20or%20I'll%20be%20homeless.%26quot%3B%20That%20comment%20made%20the%20conversation%20awkward%2C%20and%20while%20it%20may%20have%20been%20true%20and%20something%20the%20candidate%20was%20genuinely%20struggling%20with%2C%20it%20wasn't%20related%20to%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20you%20shouldn't%20overshare%20is%20that%20you%20don't%20have%20other%20job%20options%20available%20to%20you.%20%C2%A0This%20could%20lead%20to%20your%20being%20taken%20advantage%20of%20by%20an%20employer%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20for%20compensation%20negotiations.%20If%20they%20know%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20other%20options%2C%20they%20will%20likely%20low-ball%20you%20%E2%80%94%20they%20know%20they%20can%20get%20you%20for%20less%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20keep%20the%20company%20thinking%20you%20have%20other%20options%2C%20it%20may%20prompt%20a%20sense%20of%20urgency%20on%20their%20end%20and%20get%20back%20to%20you%20quicker%20(we%20all%20know%20they%20can%20sometimes%20take%20forever).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20keep%20your%20cards%20close%20to%20your%20chest%20and%20be%20tactful.%20Sharing%20less%20personal%20details%20is%20best%2C%20so%20remember%20to%20keep%20your%20answers%20concise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Accepting%20the%20job%20offer%20immediately%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20receive%20a%20job%20offer%2C%20don't%20accept%20it%20immediately%20over%20the%20phone.%20Understand%20that%20if%20a%20company%20is%20offering%20you%20a%20role%2C%20they%20want%20you%2C%20and%20you%20can%20wait%20a%20day%20or%20two%20to%20decide.%20Make%20them%20sweat%20because%20you%20want%20to%20be%20in%20the%20power%20position%2C%20and%20push%20back%20at%20least%20once%20on%20something%20that's%20negotiable%2C%20like%20base%20salary%2C%20equity%2C%20sign-on%20bonus%2C%20or%20vacation%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20not%20heard%20of%20an%20offer%20being%20rescinded%20because%20someone%20asked%20for%20slightly%20more%20money%20than%20what%20was%20initially%20presented.%20Your%20recruiter%20should%20be%20your%20advocate%2C%20and%20the%20worst%20they%20can%20say%20is%20no.%20Just%20make%20sure%20your%20ask%20aligns%20with%20the%20compensation%20expectations%20you%20outlined%20for%20them%20in%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Following%20up%20daily%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20being%20ghosted%20after%20your%20interview%20or%20if%20the%20communication%20is%20sporadic%2C%20follow%20up%20with%20the%20recruiter%2C%20but%20don't%20do%20it%20excessively.%20Instead%2C%20reach%20out%20once%20every%20one%20or%20two%20weeks%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20long%20the%20process%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20reach%20out%2C%20have%20a%20specific%20ask.%20For%20example%2C%20don't%20just%20ask%20for%20feedback%2C%20but%20ask%20something%20like%3A%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BWe%20spoke%20about%20%5Bspecific%20topic%5D%20and%20I%20have%20some%20additional%20thoughts.%20Is%20it%20possible%20to%20send%20those%20to%20you%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20said%2C%20you%20need%20to%20read%20the%20room.%20I%20tell%20candidates%20that%20I%20will%20reach%20out%20to%20them%20if%20there's%20an%20update.%20Personally%2C%20if%20the%20hiring%20process%20is%20taking%20longer%20than%20a%20week%2C%20I%20will%20reach%20out%20to%20them%20to%20tell%20them%20I%20don't%20have%20any%20updates%2C%20but%20not%20all%20recruiters%20do%20that%20so%20following%20up%20with%20them%20doesn't%20hurt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you're%20a%20big%20tech%20recruiter%20with%20helpful%20tips%20to%20share%2C%20email%20Alyshia%20Hull%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aahull%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eahull%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-that-make-candidates-look-desperate-job-search-google-recruiter-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702548961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a264450edbc52a863fb37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-that-make-candidates-look-desperate-job-search-google-recruiter-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20job%20searching%2C%20an%20ex-Google%20recruiter%20says%20people%20should%20avoid%20coming%20across%20as%20desperate%20%E2%80%94%20employers%20could%20take%20advantage%20of%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alyshia%20Hull)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-that-make-candidates-look-desperate-job-search-google-recruiter-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Amaat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14154242%2FScreenshot-2023-12-14-at-3.40.36.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Amaat%20(285%2C221%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20literal%20meaning%20of%20Amaat%20tells%20us%20nothing%20about%20the%20caste.%20One%20of%20the%20dictionary%20meanings%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98amaat%E2%80%99%20is%20someone%20who%20has%20never%20been%20defeated.%20But%20that%20meaning%20does%20not%20suit%20the%20reality%20of%20this%20caste%20group.%20This%20is%20because%20if%20it%20was%20true%2C%20they%20would%20be%20treated%20like%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20of%20the%20Hindu%20religion.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20they%20were%20considered%20Brahmins%20who%20had%20remained%20undefeated%20for%20centuries%20%E2%80%93%20except%20in%20the%20battle%20of%20Bhima-Koregaon%20in%201818.%20It%20is%20also%20possible%20that%20they%20were%20once%20warriors%20like%20the%20Rajputs.%20But%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20present%20social%20status%2C%20all%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20look%20down%20upon%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20359px)%2085vw%2C%20359px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22359%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22514%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20who%20are%20the%20Amaats%3F%20Are%20they%20really%20Brahmins%20ostracised%20by%20superior%20Brahmins%3F%20Or%20are%20they%20Rajputs%20who%20have%20been%20sidelined%20by%20the%20ruling%20Rajputs%20themselves%3F%20There%20is%20no%20information%20available%20about%20this%20caste%20in%20history.%20The%20ethnographic%20study%20of%20this%20caste%20also%20does%20not%20offer%20any%20clear%20conclusions.%20Sometimes%20it%20appears%20as%20if%20their%20existence%20is%20part%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20theory.%20This%20is%20because%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20are%20generally%20not%20poor%20%E2%80%93%20except%20a%20few.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocially%2C%20the%20Brahmins%20and%20Rajputs%20may%20treat%20them%20as%20inferior%20and%20not%20mix%20with%20them%20or%20form%20matrimonial%20alliances%20but%20ordinary%20Amaats%20consider%20themselves%20equal%20to%20these%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20groups%20in%20status.%20In%20Bihar%20they%20are%20included%20in%20the%20backward%20class%20group%20and%20enjoy%20the%20benefits%20of%20reservation.%20But%20they%20are%20not%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20find%20themselves%20in%20such%20a%20scenario.%20The%20Nautiyals%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20also%20consider%20themselves%20Brahmins%2C%20but%20are%20under%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20category.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20who%20are%20they%20really%3F%20The%20name%20Amaat%20might%20also%20be%20a%20corruption%20of%20the%20word%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98amaatya%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20means%20%E2%80%98companion%E2%80%99.%20A%20companion%20can%20be%20of%20two%20types%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20king.%20One%20is%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20security%20guard%20and%20the%20other%20is%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20minister.%20%E2%80%98Amaatya%E2%80%99%20also%20means%20%E2%80%98minister%E2%80%99.%20During%20the%20time%20of%20Chandragupta%20Maurya%2C%20Chanakya%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98Amaatya%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20theory%20does%20not%20shed%20light%20on%20who%20the%20Amaat%20are.%20If%20they%20are%20security%20guards%2C%20they%20might%20be%20Rajput%20and%20if%20they%20are%20ministers%2C%20they%20might%20be%20connected%20to%20Brahmins.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20thoughtfully%20crafted%20secret.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMegasthenes%20has%20written%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20them.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20doors%20to%20reach%20higher%20positions%20were%20closed%20for%20people%20of%20lower%20castes.%20Only%20people%20from%20a%20professional%20class%20were%20appointed%20to%20the%20judiciary%20and%20executive.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Katyayan%20also%20emphasised%2C%20%E2%80%9CAmaatya%20should%20be%20of%20Brahmin%20caste%20only.%20Amaatya%20means%20minister%2C%20which%20is%20made%20up%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emantrin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emantrin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20means%20mantra%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMundakupanishad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Amaatra%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20the%20fourth%20state%20of%20meditation%2C%20which%20is%20also%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esamadhi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20inconsistencies%20in%20this%20theory.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20concept%20of%20Nirguna%20or%20god%20being%20non-dual%20has%20not%20existed%20in%20Hinduism.%20In%20this%20religion%2C%20body%20and%20soul%20are%20given%20importance%20in%20two%20different%20forms.%20But%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20Nirguna%20and%20Advaita%2C%20one%20can%20say%20that%20those%20Brahmins%20who%20are%20not%20idol%20worshippers%20can%20be%20called%20Amaat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Indian%20and%20foreign%20scholars%20have%20written%20about%20them.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20the%20journal%20published%20by%20Bihar%20and%20Orissa%20Research%20Society%20in%201919%2C%20Amaat%20has%20been%20described%20as%20a%20pure%20priest%20of%20the%20king.%20Earlier%20in%201909%2C%20in%20their%20book%20about%20castes%20in%20India%2C%20Edgar%20Thurston%20and%20K.%20Rangchari%20stated%20that%20Amaats%20do%20not%20eat%20anything%20touched%20even%20by%20upper%20caste%20Brahmins.%20According%20to%20them%2C%20Amaats%20belong%20to%20the%20Shaiva%20sect%20and%20in%20the%20same%20temple%20where%20Jangam%20Brahmins%20(belonging%20to%20the%20Jangam%20Shaiva%20sect%20and%20who%20are%20the%20highest%20class%20Brahmins)%20perform%20the%20duties%20of%20priests%20of%20Shivalinga%2C%20Amaats%20enjoy%20the%20status%20of%20the%20priests%20of%20Bhairava.%20Bhairava%20have%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20Hindu%20mythology.%20Bhairavas%20are%20given%20a%20place%20in%20the%20temple%20premises%20but%20not%20the%20main%20sanctum%20where%20Brahmins%20run%20the%20show.%20The%20property%20of%20the%20Amaat%20also%20lies%20outside%20the%20sanctum%20sanctorum.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Tribes%20and%20Castes%20of%20Bengal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20in%201891%2C%20Risley%20wrote%20that%20Amaats%20served%20as%20domestic%20servants.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKashi%20Prasad%20Jaiswal%2C%20a%20renowned%20historian%20of%20Bihar%2C%20has%20also%20written%20that%20during%20the%2012th%20century%2C%20the%20economics%20and%20the%20tradition%20of%20punishment%20gradually%20weakened%20and%20theology%20became%20dominant.%20Society%20fell%20into%20the%20grip%20of%20hypocrisy.%20He%20opines%20that%20due%20to%20their%20separation%20from%20the%20majority%2C%20%E2%80%98Amaatra%E2%80%99%20may%20have%20become%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20dissenter%2C%20which%20would%20later%20become%20%E2%80%98Amaat%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20while%20theorising%2C%20Jaiswal%20does%20not%20clarify%20that%20the%2012th%20century%20was%20the%20century%20when%20the%20reign%20of%20outside%20rulers%20began%20in%20India.%20It%20can%20be%20assumed%20that%20during%20that%20time%2C%20the%20dominance%20of%20Brahmins%20would%20have%20declined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20why%20would%20any%20Muslim%20ruler%20want%20to%20make%20a%20Brahmin%20his%20Amaat%20%E2%80%93%20minister%20or%20security%20guard%3F%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20Muslim%20rulers%20came%20to%20know%20about%20the%20story%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20commander%20Pushyamitra%20Shunga%20and%20how%20he%20killed%20Brihadratha%20by%20stabbing%20him%20in%20the%20back%20and%20captured%20the%20kingdom%20of%20the%20Maurya%20dynasty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20social%2C%20educational%20and%20economic%20grounds%2C%20Amaat%2C%20with%20a%20population%20of%20285%2C221%2C%20are%20unlike%20other%20backward%20castes%20or%20Dalits%20of%20Bihar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F261400%2Fbihar-caste-survey-who-are-the-amaats%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%5C%22%3EChaupal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%5C%22%3ENai%2FHajjaam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-pasi%5C%22%3EPasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-rangrez%5C%22%3ERangrez%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-who