22%3Edefines%3C%2Fa%3E%20them%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3Eany%20weapon%20or%20munition%20which%20is%20primarily%20designed%20to%20set%20fire%20to%20objects%20or%20to%20cause%20burn%20injury%20to%20persons%20through%20the%20action%20of%20flame%2C%20heat%2C%20or%20combination%20thereof%2C%20produced%20by%20a%20chemical%20reaction%20of%20a%20substance%20delivered%20on%20the%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20phosphorus%20is%20not%20illegal%20under%20international%20law%20and%20the%20law%20of%20armed%20conflict%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it%20is%20being%20used%20defensively%20as%20a%20smokescreen%20or%20as%20battlefield%20illumination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20targeted%20use%20of%20incendiary%20weapons%20directly%20against%20civilians%2C%20however%2C%20is%20illegal%20and%20could%20be%20considered%20a%20war%20crime.%20The%20use%20of%20%E2%80%9Cair-delivered%E2%80%9D%20incendiary%20weapons%20(such%20as%20white%20phosphorus%20dropped%20from%20a%20plane)%20against%20a%20military%20target%20that%20is%20in%20a%20civilian%20area%20is%20also%20prohibited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20exception%2C%20though%2C%20if%20the%20military%20target%20is%20%E2%80%9Cclearly%20separated%E2%80%9D%20from%20civilians%20and%20all%20%E2%80%9Cfeasible%20precautions%E2%80%9D%20are%20taken%20to%20limit%20incidental%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%20or%20injuries%20to%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20this%20means%20the%20targeting%20of%20either%20Hamas%20or%20Hezbollah%20is%20permissible%20as%20long%20as%20the%20white%20phosphorus%20is%20not%20air%20delivered%20and%20steps%20are%20taken%20to%20minimise%20the%20harm%20to%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Israel%20is%20accused%20of%20doing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmnesty%20International%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2Flebanon-evidence-of-israels-unlawful-use-of-white-phosphorus-in-southern-lebanon-as-cross-border-hostilities-escalate%2F%5C%22%3Ecompiled%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20indicates%20white%20phosphorus%20was%20likely%20used%20in%20a%20civilian%20setting%20(the%20Lebanese%20town%20of%20Dheira)%20in%20October.%20Residents%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Finvestigations%2F2023%2F12%2F11%2Fisrael-us-white-phosphorus-lebanon%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Israeli%20forces%20had%20shelled%20the%20town%20with%20%E2%80%9Cwhite%20phosphorus%20munitions%20for%20hours%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20reports%20need%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20to%20examine%20what%20exactly%20happened%20and%20if%20there%20was%20an%20illegal%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorous%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20or%20whether%20it%20was%20permitted%20under%20the%20guidelines%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20will%20need%20to%20determine%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20if%20white%20phosphorous%20was%20indeed%20used%20and%2C%20if%20it%20was%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20delivered%20via%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F12%2Fquestions-and-answers-israels-use-white-phosphorus-gaza-and-lebanon%5C%22%3Eairburst%20or%20a%20groundburst%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20would%20also%20need%20to%20determine%20if%20the%20forces%20took%20steps%20to%20minimise%20civilian%20harm.%20This%20a%20very%20difficult%20proposition%20in%20the%20current%20conflict%2C%20as%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20are%20known%20to%20embed%20their%20fighters%20within%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F30%2Fhuman-shield-israel-claim-hamas-command-centre-under-hospital-palestinian-civilian-gaza-city%5C%22%3Ecivilian%20population%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20direct%20targeting%20of%20civilians%20or%20indiscriminate%20use%20of%20air-delivered%20incendiary%20weapons%20would%20potentially%20qualify%20as%20a%20war%20crime%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Feng%2Fassets%2Ffiles%2Fpublications%2Ficrc-002-0173.pdf%5C%22%3EGeneva%20Conventions%20of%201949%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fog%20of%20war%2C%20it%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20to%20have%20independent%20verification%20of%20the%20actions%20of%20combatants%20on%20both%20sides%20and%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20by%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20prosecution%20of%20any%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20in%20the%20current%20conflict%20remains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhy-is-accountability-for-alleged-war-crimes-so-hard-to-achieve-in-the-israel-palestinian-conflict-160864%5C%22%3Eextremely%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20due%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20the%20fact%20Israel%20is%20not%20a%20member%20of%20the%20ICC%20and%20rejects%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%20over%20its%20territory%20and%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20are%20non-state%20entities.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F219809%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fsascha-dominik-dov-bachmann-124784%5C%22%3ESascha-Dominik%20(Dov)%20Bachmann%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20in%20Law%20and%20Co-Convener%20National%20Security%20Hub%20(University%20of%20Canberra)%20and%20Research%20Fellow%20(adjunct)%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Security%20Institute%20for%20Governance%20and%20Leadership%20in%20Africa%2C%20Faculty%20of%20Military%20Science%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University-%20NATO%20Fellow%20Asia-Pacific%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-canberra-865%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Canberra%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republis