d%20at%20encouraging%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20investment%20in%20the%20EV%20industry%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fin-a-blow-to-tesla-indian-govt-says-not-planning-to-reduce-ev-import-tax-123121400322_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fin-a-blow-to-tesla-indian-govt-says-not-planning-to-reduce-ev-import-tax-123121400322_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fin-a-blow-to-tesla-indian-govt-says-not-planning-to-reduce-ev-import-tax-123121400322_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Last%20Pillar%20of%20Indian%20Democracy%20Has%20Fallen%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13130248%2FSupreme-Court-p.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20has%20given%20a%20succession%20of%20judgements%20that%20have%20eroded%20civil%20society%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20faith%20in%20its%20readiness%20to%20uphold%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20and%20protect%20its%20secular%2C%20ethno-federal%20democracy%20from%20the%20relentless%20attack%20that%20has%20been%20launched%20upon%20it%20by%20the%20government%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah.%20But%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-zakia-jafri-command-responsibility%5C%22%3Emost%20perverse%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20previous%20decisions%20pales%20into%20insignificance%20before%20that%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3Ejudgment%20upholding%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Constitution%20on%205%2C%20August%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%2C%20and%20most%20disturbing%2C%20editorials%20that%20I%20have%20read%20in%20six%20decades%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fominously-anti-federal-on-the-supreme-courts-judgement-on-article-370-and-jks-special-status%2Farticle67628150.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20described%20how%2C%20by%20upholding%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20opened%20the%20way%20for%20his%20or%20any%20future%20government%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20without%20having%20to%20bother%20with%20getting%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20is%20simple%3A%20take%20advantage%20of%2C%20or%20create%2C%20a%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20in%20a%20state%2C%20declare%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20under%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20claim%20that%20the%20president%20(or%20governor)%20now%20has%20all%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%C2%A0%20and%20enact%20whatever%20change%20the%20state%20government%20did%20not%20want%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20in%20which%20the%20Modi%20government%20will%20use%20this%20interpretation%20of%20the%20Constitution%20needs%20no%20imagination.%20In%20three%20states%20the%20BJP-appointed%20governors%20have%20refused%20to%20give%20their%20assent%20to%20Bills%20or%20laws%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature.%20In%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20in%20a%20direct%20violation%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20refused%20to%20give%20it%20even%20after%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20returned%20to%20him%20a%20second%20time.%20This%20was%20an%20express%20violation%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20but%20one%20that%20was%20directly%20instigated%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20sent%20a%20team%20of%2040%20CBI%20officials%20to%20Kolkata%2C%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcbis-attempted-arrest-of-kolkata-police-commissioner-was-an-attack-on-federalism%5C%22%3Earrest%20a%20serving%20police%20commissioner%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20state%20government%20and%20bring%20him%20to%20Delhi%20for%20interrogation.%20Its%20attempt%20was%20foiled%20only%20because%20there%20was%20an%20elected%C2%A0%20state%20government%20whose%20police%20rose%20in%20defence%20of%20their%20commissioner%20and%20%E2%80%98arrested%E2%80%99%20the%20CBI%20officials%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Will%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20Article%20370%20Judgment%20Mean%20for%20Politics%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-will-the-supreme-courts-article-370-judgment-mean-for-politics-in-jk%5C%22%3EWhat%20Will%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Article%20370%20Judgment%20Mean%20for%20Politics%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20taken%20advantage%20of%20its%20already%20being%20a%20union%20territory%20to%20arrest%20no%20less%20august%20a%20personage%20than%20its%20elected%20deputy%20chief%20minister%2C%20Manish%20Sisodia%2C%20and%20has%20been%20holding%20him%20without%20bail%20and%20despite%20being%20unable%20to%20frame%20a%20charge%20against%20him%20for%20ten%20months.%20Not%20Satisfied%20with%20that%2C%20Modi%20is%20now%20attempting%20to%20do%20the%20same%20with%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20actions%20of%20a%20tyrant%2C%20not%20of%20the%20elected%20leader%20of%20a%20democratic%20government%2C%20and%20all%20have%20been%20taken%C2%A0%20before%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20his%20colleagues%E2%80%99%20eyes.%20How%20long%20do%20they%20think%20it%20will%20be%20before%20Modi%20begins%20to%20use%20the%20freedom%20their%20verdict%20has%20given%20him%2C%20to%20start%20overturning%20opposition%20governments%20in%20order%20to%20bend%20the%20whole%20of%20India%20to%20his%20and%20his%20Hindutva%20colleagues%E2%80%99%20will%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20justify%20its%20decision%2C%20the%20bench%20has%20put%20forward%20two%20other%20supporting%20arguments.%20The%20first%20is%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20placed%20in%20part%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20titled%20%E2%80%9CTemporary%2C%20Transitional%20and%20Special%20Provisions%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%20it%20was%20never%20meant%20to%20be%20permanent.%20So%20all%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20done%20is%20to%20close%20the%20chapter%20on%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20that%20over%20the%20decades%20since%20the%20accession%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20laws%20have%20in%20any%20case%20been%20brought%20in%20line%20progressively%20with%20those%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20So%20as%20the%20government%20has%20argued%2C%20the%20autonomy%20shielded%20by%20Article%20370%20had%20been%20been%20%E2%80%98gradually%20eroded%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20so%20deliberate%20a%20misreading%20of%20the%20Constitution%20that%20it%20leaves%20one%20gasping%20for%20breath.%20How%20could%20the%20learned%20judges%20not%20know%20that%20%E2%80%98temporary%E2%80%99%20had%20to%20be%20read%20within%20its%20temporal%20and%20political%20context%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20was%20drafted%20in%201948-49%20and%20adopted%20by%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20on%20November%2026%2C%201949.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20India%20was%20still%20a%20dominion%20of%20the%20British%20Commonwealth.%20The%20princely%20state%20of%20Kashmir%20had%20acceded%20to%20India%20but%20two-fifths%20of%20it%20was%20occupied%20by%20Pakistan%20and%20war%20was%20still%20raging%20there.%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20India%20had%20been%20confirmed%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%2C%20subject%20to%20a%20plebiscite.%20But%20Pakistan%20had%20refused%20to%20vacate%20occupied%20Kashmir%2C%20because%20it%20knew%2C%20as%20British%20high%20commissioner%20to%20Pakistan%20Sir%20Patrick%20Graftey-Smith%20had%20reported%20to%20London%20from%20Karachi%20as%20early%20as%20October%201947%20when%20the%20invasion%20of%20Kashmir%20had%20just%20begun%2C%20that%20it%20would%20lose%20it%20if%20one%20were%20to%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Governors'%20Pocket%20Veto%20Compromises%20Constitutional%20Probity%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgovernors-pocket-veto-compromises-constitutional-probity%5C%22%3EGovernors%E2%80%99%20Pocket%20Veto%20Compromises%20Constitutional%20Probity%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20knew%20that%20substantial%20amendments%20would%20be%20needed%20when%20the%20two%20parts%20of%20Kashmir%20were%20reunited.%20Thus%20%3Cem%3Eit%20was%20the%20boundaries%20of%20Kashmir%20that%20were%20temporary%20when%20the%20Constitution%20was%20adopted.%20%3C%2Fem%3ESince%20%E2%80%98Azad%E2%80%99%20Kashmir%20is%20now%20generally%20accepted%20as%20a%20province%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20the%20ceasefire%20line%20has%20become%20the%20de-facto%20boundary%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20word%20temporary%20has%20lost%20its%20meaning.%20It%20was%20the%20worst%20kind%20of%20sleight%20of%20hand%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20have%20given%20this%20term%20a%20wholly%20different%20meaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20other%20justification%20for%20its%20verdict%20is%20equally%20flawed.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20over%20the%20past%20seven%20decades%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20laws%20and%20constitutional%20safeguards%20have%20been%20brought%20more%20and%20more%20in%20line%20with%20those%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20The%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20had%20brought%20only%20defence%2C%20foreign%20policy%20and%20communications%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20Central%20power.%20It%20was%20the%20Delhi%20Agreement%20of%201952%2C%20overseen%20by%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%2C%20that%20began%20the%20integration%20of%20government%20in%20all%20spheres%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20how%20comprehensive%20it%20was%20can%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20range%20of%20subjects%20covered%3A%20These%20included%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20head%20of%20the%20state%3B%20the%20extension%20of%20all%20the%20civic%20and%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens%20of%20India%20to%20persons%20domiciled%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%3B%20and%20extension%20of%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20integrated%20the%20fiscal%20system%20of%20the%20state%20with%20that%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India%2C%20thereby%20giving%20Kashmiris%20full%20and%20free%20access%20to%20the%20vast%20Indian%20market.%20Finally%20it%20extended%20key%20symbols%20of%20statehood%20like%20the%20national%20flag%2C%20and%20the%20emergency%20powers%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%20to%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20agreement%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20integration%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20in%201963%2C%20Nehru%20said%20that%20Article%20370%20has%20been%20eroded%20and%20the%20process%20of%20gradual%20erosion%20was%20going%20on.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20home%20minister%20Gulzari%20Lal%20Nanda%2C%20described%20article%20370%20as%20a%20tunnel%20to%20take%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20released%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20from%20incarceration%20and%20allowed%20him%20to%20resume%20his%20chief%20ministership%20of%20Kashmir%2C%2023%20constitutional%20orders%20had%20been%20promulgated%20to%20further%20integrate%20the%20state%20into%20the%20Indian%20Union%2C%20and%20262%20Union%20laws%20had%20been%20applied%20to%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20chosen%20to%20ignore%20is%20that%20all%20this%20was%20done%20with%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20governments%20of%20the%20time.%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20had%20signed%20the%20Delhi%20agreement%20only%20after%20convening%20a%20constituent%20Assembly%20with%2075%20members%2C%20to%20approve%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decades%20that%20followed%2C%20more%20and%20more%20all-India%20laws%20and%20provisions%20were%20extended%20to%20Kashmir%20as%20well%20with%20the%20full%20consent%2C%20often%20at%20the%20request%20of%2C%20the%20Kashmir%20government.%20As%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20talks%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20special%20representative%2C%20G.%20Parthasarathy%2C%20before%20returning%C2%A0%20to%20power%20showed%2C%20there%20was%20next%20to%20nothing%20left%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20process%20was%20a%20world%20away%20from%20the%20sleight%20of%20hand%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20used%20in%202019%2C%20to%20%E2%80%98complete%E2%80%99%20the%20integration.%20The%20contrast%20between%20%E2%80%98erosion%20by%20consent%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98erosion%20through%20brute%20force%E2%80%99%20was%20vividly%20demonstrated%20by%20the%20weeks-long%20curfews%2C%20the%20complete%20shut%20down%20of%20internet%20services%2C%20and%20the%20paralysis%20of%20transport%20even%20afterwards%20that%20forced%20people%20catching%20flights%20out%20of%20Kashmir%20to%20walk%20kilometres%20to%20get%20to%20the%20airport.%20For%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20have%20glossed%20over%20this%20stark%20and%20humiliating%20difference%20is%20inexcusable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20after%20two%20foreign%20governments%20have%20accused%20the%20Modi%20government%20of%20carrying%20out%20or%20planning%20extra-judicial%20killings%20on%20their%20soil%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20sole%20remaining%20pillar%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20once%20vaunted%2C%20and%20much%20envied%2C%20democracy%20has%20finally%20fallen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrem%20Shankar%20Jha%20is%20a%20veteran%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-last-pillar-of-indian-democracy-has-fallen%23_ftnref1%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702534737000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13130248%2FSupreme-Court-p.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-last-pillar-of-indian-democracy-has-fallen%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20upholding%20the%20Article%20370%20decision%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20opened%20the%20way%20for%20the%20government%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20without%20having%20to%20bother%20with%20getting%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A54%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-last-pillar-of-indian-democracy-has-fallen%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Park%20Seo%20Joon's%20adorable%20'aegyo'%20moment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702534631000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105980906%2Cimgsize-18958.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fthrowback-when-park-seo-joons-adorable-aegyo-moment-from-fight-for-my-way-went-viral%2Farticleshow%2F105980992.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105980992.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%202017%20drama%20'Fight%20For%20My%20Way'%20starring%20Park%20Seo%20Joon%20and%20Kim%20Ji%20Won%20gained%20international%20fame.%20The%20series%20started%20with%20modest%20ratings%20but%20grew%20in%20popularity%2C%20reaching%20a%20remarkable%2013-14%25.%20The%20chemistry%20between%20the%20lead%20actors%20earned%20them%20the%20Best%20Couple%20Award%20at%20the%20KBS%20Drama%20Awards%202017.%20Park%20Seo%20Joon%20was%20recognized%20with%20the%20Outstanding%20Korean%20Actor%20Award%20at%20the%20Seoul%20International%20Drama%20Awards.%20One%20scene%20that%20stood%20out%20was%20the%20aegyo%20moment%2C%20where%20Kim%20Ji%20Won's%20character%20used%20aegyo%20to%20persuade%20Park%20Seo%20Joon's%20character.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fthrowback-when-park-seo-joons-adorable-aegyo-moment-from-fight-for-my-way-went-viral%2Farticleshow%2F105980992.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MP%3A%20Newly%20Sworn-in%20CM%20Places%20Curbs%20on%20Loudspeakers%20at%20Religious%20Places%2C%20Sale%20of%20Meat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14110618%2FEffect-29.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20newly%C2%A0sworn-in%20chief%20minister%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Mohan%20Yadav%2C%20has%20placed%20curbs%20on%20the%20use%20of%20loudspeakers%20at%20religious%20places%20and%20the%20sale%20of%20meat%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYadav%20was%20administered%20the%20oath%20of%20office%20by%20governor%20Mangubhai%20C.%20Patel%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20galaxy%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20leaders%2C%20including%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20December%2013%2C%20Bhopal.%20With%20Yadav%20taking%20over%20the%20reins%20of%20the%20state%20government%2C%20it%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%2018-year%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20hours%20of%20assuming%20charge%2C%20Yadav%20presided%20over%20his%20first%20Cabinet%20meeting%2C%20following%20which%20he%20issued%20directions%20to%20the%20effect%20that%20loudspeakers%2FDJs%2C%20etc.%2C%20can%20be%20used%20only%20as%20per%20the%20prescribed%20norms%20at%20any%20type%20of%20religious%20place%20or%20in%20public%20places.%20Known%20for%20his%20communal%20rhetoric%20and%20aggressive%20Hindutva%2C%20Yadav%2C%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20government%2C%20issued%20directives%20to%20%E2%80%9Cban%20illegal%20buying%20and%20selling%20of%20meat%2C%20fish%2C%20etc.%2C%20in%20the%20open%20without%20licence%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintensive%20campaign%20will%20be%20launched%E2%80%9D%20to%20this%20effect%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fnew-cm-mohan-yadav-first-order-prohibits-loudspeakers-religious-places-permissible-limits-9067201%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cabinet%20meeting%20was%20attended%20by%20Jagdish%20Devda%20and%20Rajendra%20Shukla%2C%20who%20were%20sworn%20in%20alongside%20Yadav%20as%20his%20deputies.%20Other%20ministers%20of%20the%20state%20cabinet%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20announced%20and%20sworn%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20issue%20of%20loudspeakers%2C%20the%20Cabinet%20decided%20to%20form%20flying%20squads%20across%20all%20districts%20to%20check%20noise%20pollution%20and%20the%20illegal%20use%20of%20loudspeakers.%20These%20squads%20will%20regularly%20and%20randomly%20inspect%20religious%20and%20public%20places%20where%20loudspeakers%20are%20used.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20violation%2C%20authorities%20have%20been%20ordered%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter%20within%20a%20maximum%20of%20three%20days%20and%20submit%20the%20report%20to%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cabinet%20also%20decided%20to%20come%20up%20with%20%E2%80%9Cfood%20safety%20rules%E2%80%9D%20to%20ensure%20meat%20shops%20and%20shops%20selling%20eggs%20adhere%20to%20guidelines%2C%20by%20creating%20awareness%20among%20the%20public%20as%20well%20as%20shop%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20the%20upcoming%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20fortune%E2%80%9D%2C%20Yadav%20told%20the%20media%2C%20after%20the%20Cabinet%20meeting%2C%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20will%20welcome%20all%20the%20Ram%20devotees%20in%20every%20district%2C%20who%20are%20en%20route%20to%20the%20Ram%20mandir%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmohan-yadav-little-known-outside-ujjan-bjps-cm-pick-for-mp-baffles-party-leaders-cadres%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20Yadav%20as%20chief%20minister%20baffled%20both%20party%20leaders%20and%20cadres.%20The%20BJP%20decided%20to%20go%20with%20Yadav%20(54)%2C%20who%20is%20relatively%20unknown%20outside%20of%20Ujjain.%20The%20party%20high%20command%20sprang%20a%20surprise%20by%20ignoring%20half%20a%20dozen%20other%20claimants%20for%20the%20post%2C%20much%20senior%20to%20Yadav%2C%20including%20Kailash%20Vijayvargiya%2C%20Narendra%20Singh%20Tomar%2C%20and%20Prahlad%20Singh%20Patel.%20Except%20for%20former%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%2C%20none%20said%20to%20have%20had%20prior%20information%20about%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20anointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidered%20a%20committed%20footsoldier%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%2C%20Yadav%20has%C2%A0thrived%20financially%20and%20politically%20by%20mouthing%20provocative%20language%20against%20Muslims.%20His%20strong%20pro-Hindutva%20stance%20brought%20him%20close%20to%20the%20Sangh.%20The%20RSS%20is%20said%20to%20have%20a%20major%20say%20in%20his%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702534529000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14110618%2FEffect-29.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmp-newly-sworn-in-cm-orders-curbs-on-loudspeakers-at-religious-pl